This evening class is hosted by On The Move Physical Therapy <b><span style="color: #45818e;"><a href="http://www.onthemovephysio.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.onthemovephysio.com</a></span></b> specializing in Physical Therapy, Sports and Dance Rehab and Pilates and taught by Hazel Wood, Master ChiRunning &amp; ChiWalking Instructor. You will learn how to set up good posture and engage core muscles for efficient and mindful movement.  Learn the basic skills of ChiRunning &amp; ChiWalking that you can apply right away.   For information on Hazel and ChiRunning visit <a href="http://stridebystride.com/">www.stridebystride.com</a>

&nbsp;
<h2 align="left"></h2>

Come learn the basic components of the ChiRunning technique and move well for life! In the span of four hours, you will be guided through many exercises and drills designed to leave you with a clear sense of what the ChiRunning technique feels like in your body. We will not be doing lots of running (contrary to what you might imagine), so no matter what condition you’re in, have no fear. We will spend time alternating between demonstrations, fun exercises, and technique drills… the nature of the day will be relaxed, full, and inspiring.

COVID19 Protocol: The instructor and participants will be required to follow the current recommendations on the dates of in-person sessions. The instructor will contact the participants with the most current recommendations prior to those dates.

